---
title: Vegan Sweet Potato Cakes with Lime-Pickled Onion, Guacamole, Rice & Beans
description: Fresh out of vegan dinner ideas? We got you! Try these smoky, Mexican-spiced black bean and sweet potato cakes that are crispy on the outside, sweet and tender on the inside, and studded with zingy red onion. Shallow-fry them until crisp and golden and serve over a fluffy mound of rice and beans. Dollop with guacamole, and finish with a tangy tangle of lime-pickled onion, a drizzle of hot sauce, and a shower of cilantro. Keep us in your back pocket, and you’ll never run out of recipe ideas!
